name: Ada Lovelace
description: English mathematician who wrote notes on Babbage's Analytical Engine and is often credited with the first algorithm intended to be carried out by a machine.

name: Alan Turing
description: British mathematician and logician; founding figure in theoretical computer science and artificial intelligence; led cryptanalysis work at Bletchley Park during WWII.

name: Grace Hopper
description: American computer scientist and U.S. Navy rear admiral; pioneer of programming languages and compiler development, and influential in the creation and adoption of COBOL.

name: Linus Torvals
description: Linus Benedict Torvalds[a] (born 28 December 1969) is a Finnish and American software engineer who is the creator and lead developer of the Linux kernel. He also created the distributed version control system Git.
